tellraw @s {"text":"\n---------- Rauchergames Datapack Setup Guide ----------","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"Overwiew: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Rauchergames (don't ask about the name) consists of, so far, 4 game modes (plus one for testing), that are all played with up to 12 players divided into 2 teams (while it is possible to play completely alone, i recommend at least 2 players per team). Each player can choose from one of 8 kits with unique stats and abilities. Win by completing the game mode-specific objective. Make sure you have the Rauch Texturepack installed.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting Out: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"If this is the first time the datapack is active, you wil be asked to define the position of the lobby. The lobby is the place players return to after a game. With the spawnegg, just right click on a block at the desired location. If you somehow lose the item, simply reload the world (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/reload","color":"gold"},{"text":").","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdding Maps: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"In order to play, you first need to add a map. To edit game settings, add maps etc. you need to be an admin. You can make a player an admin by using the command (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag playername add admin","color":"gold"},{"text":"). To remove admin rights, do (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag playername remove admin","color":"gold"},{"text":"). Admins have access to the Settings Book in their first hotbar slot. From here you can change game modes, maps and more. Add a map by going to the 3rd page and clicking on \"Add Map\". A Guide will be available there, too.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nKits: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Before Starting, each player has to select a kit using the book called \"Kit Selector/Settings\". You can see their stats and abilities by hovering over the name. Click to Select. Each class has three abilities, R, Q and F. In game, you can activate R by right-clicking and Q and F by pressing the respective key on your keyboard. All abilities have a cooldown.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nGame Modes: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"You can choose a game mode using the Settings-Book. Hovering over the name will show information about the mode.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nOther Players: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"When first joining, other players are not part of the lobby (they don't have the Kit Selector etc.). Use \"Move Everyone To Lobby\" in the Settings Book to fix this.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting a Game: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"After having selected a kit and a map (using the 2nd page of the \"Settings\"-Book), right-click with the green item called \"Ready\". This will move you to the queue. Here all players can choose a team while admins can start the game using the teams chosen or with random teams. Make sure everyone that wants to play is in queue before starting. Have Fun!","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"------------------- Setup Guide End -------------------","color":"green"}
